1
00:00:07,067 --> 00:00:08,500
<i> I do know a doctor!</i>

2
00:00:08,500 --> 00:00:10,733
<i>She's nice and abides
by the law!</i>

3
00:00:10,967 --> 00:00:14,633
<i>Doctor, let me just say that
you know me.</i>

4
00:00:14,633 --> 00:00:16,433
<i>I don't associate myself
with criminals.</i>

5
00:00:16,433 --> 00:00:18,100
<i> Jalil is not a bad person.</i>

6
00:00:18,100 --> 00:00:19,467
<i> Thank you so much.</i>

7
00:00:22,500 --> 00:00:23,867
<i> That's the doctor's son?</i>

8
00:00:23,933 --> 00:00:25,267
He's the one who caught Father.

9
00:00:25,267 --> 00:00:27,400
<i>He's also the one
who's after Jalil!</i>

10
00:00:27,400 --> 00:00:28,600
<i> Marcus, hey.</i>

11
00:00:28,667 --> 00:00:31,200
<i>I'll be there soon.
I'm at the gate.</i>

12
00:00:31,333 --> 00:00:33,900
<i> My son who's from the SID
is on his way home.</i>

13
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:34,967
<i> Who is it, son?</i>

14
00:00:35,133 --> 00:00:36,633
<i> He's from Datu Rahman's town.</i>

15
00:00:36,767 --> 00:00:38,233
<i>I had an encounter
with him earlier.</i>

16
00:00:38,367 --> 00:00:40,333
<i>He's the one who can answer
my questions.</i>

17
00:00:40,467 --> 00:00:42,767
<i>That Marcus Reyes
is too stubborn!</i>

18
00:00:42,933 --> 00:00:45,400
<i>Does he want to be fired
once and for all?!</i>

19
00:00:45,533 --> 00:00:47,100
<i> He needs to learn his lesson</i>

20
00:00:47,100 --> 00:00:49,233
<i> and even you, Agent Angeles!</i>

21
00:00:49,367 --> 00:00:52,000
The only way to solve this case
<i> once and for all</i>

22
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:53,300
is to bring your top agent back.

23
00:00:53,300 --> 00:00:56,133
<i>Are you our ally
or their accomplice?</i>

24
00:00:56,267 --> 00:00:57,600
[BOTH SHOUTING]

25
00:00:57,767 --> 00:01:00,267
<i>You animal.
I'll get you someday.</i>

26
00:01:00,433 --> 00:01:04,100
<i>Omar, good thing
the doctor you know is kind.</i>

27
00:01:04,200 --> 00:01:05,467
<i> It's just so unfortunate</i>

28
00:01:05,467 --> 00:01:07,000
<i>that her other son
died at such a young age.</i>

29
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:08,500
<i> Gabriel!</i>

30
00:01:08,733 --> 00:01:10,167
<i>If anyone can point out
the identity</i>

31
00:01:10,167 --> 00:01:12,800
<i> or whereabouts of this man,</i>

32
00:01:12,800 --> 00:01:14,300
<i> you may report it</i>

33
00:01:14,300 --> 00:01:16,667
<i>to the contact information
on your screens right now.</i>

34
00:01:21,500 --> 00:01:28,467
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

35
00:01:38,567 --> 00:01:40,633
Huh? Isn't that Jalil?

36
00:01:40,900 --> 00:01:42,667
The bounty on his head is huge!

37
00:01:43,500 --> 00:01:44,867
Two million pesos!

38
00:01:45,167 --> 00:01:46,300
With such a huge amount,

39
00:01:46,400 --> 00:01:48,300
there's no doubt a lot of people
will be tempted to find him.

40
00:01:48,400 --> 00:01:50,700
This Datu Rahman
Abubakar person,

41
00:01:51,100 --> 00:01:53,100
isn't he the one
who visits Sir Omar's place

42
00:01:53,100 --> 00:01:54,067
every now and then?

43
00:01:54,067 --> 00:01:57,133
Yes. Then when Datu Rahman
got arrested,

44
00:01:57,333 --> 00:01:59,833
Jalil suddenly arrived
in this town.

45
00:02:00,167 --> 00:02:01,467
And he even got shot!

46
00:02:01,600 --> 00:02:02,667
If that's the case,

47
00:02:03,067 --> 00:02:04,700
those two are connected
to each other.

48
00:02:06,167 --> 00:02:08,200
- If not...
- Oh, come on...

49
00:02:08,200 --> 00:02:10,800
What kind of mess did we get
ourselves into this time?

50
00:02:11,433 --> 00:02:13,833
It seems a criminal
has infiltrated our town!

51
00:02:14,733 --> 00:02:17,267
The police won't ever
leave us alone now.

52
00:02:17,733 --> 00:02:19,567
Hold on, Miss Zubina.

53
00:02:19,700 --> 00:02:21,733
The guy hasn't even
been tried yet.

54
00:02:21,733 --> 00:02:23,433
He hasn't even
been sentenced yet.

55
00:02:23,700 --> 00:02:25,000
But you're already judging him.

56
00:02:25,133 --> 00:02:26,233
True. Plus,

57
00:02:26,467 --> 00:02:28,667
we know how Sir Omar is.

58
00:02:28,933 --> 00:02:31,733
If this Jalil guy
really is a bad person,

59
00:02:32,533 --> 00:02:36,133
he wouldn't have
enabled him, would he?

60
00:02:36,133 --> 00:02:43,100
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

61
00:02:44,867 --> 00:02:46,567
[CAR DOOR OPENS]

62
00:02:49,767 --> 00:02:51,200
[CAR DOOR CLOSES]

63
00:03:05,767 --> 00:03:12,733
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

64
00:03:13,400 --> 00:03:15,400
[HURRIED KNOCKING ON DOOR]

65
00:03:15,400 --> 00:03:16,633
- Just a minute!
- Jamilah.

66
00:03:17,500 --> 00:03:19,467
- Uncle...
- I'll handle it.

67
00:03:24,533 --> 00:03:26,300
- What's going on?
- We already know the truth.

68
00:03:26,667 --> 00:03:28,133
You are Datu Rahman's son.

69
00:03:28,333 --> 00:03:29,667
You're also wanted
by the police

70
00:03:29,667 --> 00:03:31,100
with a bounty on your head.

71
00:03:31,300 --> 00:03:38,267
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

72
00:03:50,200 --> 00:03:52,067
I'm begging you all.

73
00:03:52,300 --> 00:03:53,567
Please, don't get them involved.

74
00:03:53,900 --> 00:03:54,867
Just come for me alone!

75
00:03:57,333 --> 00:03:58,767
We all talked about it earlier.

76
00:04:00,133 --> 00:04:02,467
We believe you are not
a bad person.

77
00:04:02,667 --> 00:04:04,667
That's why no one
will bother you.

78
00:04:04,833 --> 00:04:08,167
They targeted your village
even if you did nothing wrong.

79
00:04:08,333 --> 00:04:09,433
Why?

80
00:04:09,700 --> 00:04:13,033
Because it's so easy for them
to blame us, Muslims?

81
00:04:13,700 --> 00:04:15,033
Don't worry.

82
00:04:15,200 --> 00:04:16,833
We'll protect you.

83
00:04:18,233 --> 00:04:19,500
We're on your side.

84
00:04:21,300 --> 00:04:22,267
Thank you.

85
00:04:24,700 --> 00:04:26,200
Thank you.

86
00:04:29,367 --> 00:04:33,367
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

87
00:04:33,367 --> 00:04:35,733
- [BOTH GRUNTING]
- [BLOW LANDS]

88
00:04:38,867 --> 00:04:40,833
- [CRASHES LOUDLY]
- [GROANS IN PAIN]

89
00:04:43,767 --> 00:04:45,833
[GROANING]

90
00:04:50,667 --> 00:04:52,000
- [GROANING]
- [JALIL GRUNTING]

91
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:54,933
[WALL CRASHING]

92
00:04:54,933 --> 00:05:01,867
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

93
00:05:07,733 --> 00:05:09,533
[MARCUS]<i> There are signs
</i> of struggle.

94
00:05:10,633 --> 00:05:11,767
<i> Which means that...</i>

95
00:05:12,567 --> 00:05:14,400
Datu Rahman has been kidnapped.

96
00:05:15,400 --> 00:05:16,900
<i> He's certainly still alive.</i>

97
00:05:18,133 --> 00:05:19,533
<i> Because if not,</i>

98
00:05:20,100 --> 00:05:22,367
<i>his corpse would be here
to welcome me.</i>

99
00:05:22,367 --> 00:05:29,267
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

100
00:05:36,933 --> 00:05:41,700
[GLASSES CRACKING]

101
00:05:44,633 --> 00:05:47,400
- [ALL GRUNTING]
- [BLOWS LANDING]

102
00:05:47,733 --> 00:05:50,333
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

103
00:05:50,333 --> 00:05:52,933
- [ALL GRUNTING]
- [BLOWS LANDING]

104
00:05:52,933 --> 00:05:54,433
[LOUD THUD]

105
00:05:56,800 --> 00:06:01,567
<i> Let go of me! Let go of me!</i>

106
00:06:01,567 --> 00:06:02,667
[MASKED MAN 1 GROANING]

107
00:06:02,667 --> 00:06:03,900
- [LOUD THWACK]
- [GLASS SHATTERS]

108
00:06:05,300 --> 00:06:06,433
<i> Argh...</i>

109
00:06:06,733 --> 00:06:09,500
[DATU RAHMAN GROANING]

110
00:06:09,533 --> 00:06:11,100
- [MASKED MAN]<i> Let's go!
</i> - Get your hands off me!

111
00:06:11,267 --> 00:06:12,500
<i>- Come on!
- Argh...</i>

112
00:06:13,133 --> 00:06:14,633
<i> Just let me go!</i>

113
00:06:15,167 --> 00:06:17,933
[GRUNTING, GROANING]

114
00:06:22,833 --> 00:06:25,500
[MARCUS] Datu Rahman
remains captive to this day

115
00:06:26,467 --> 00:06:28,567
<i>because they need
something from him.</i>

116
00:06:29,667 --> 00:06:31,000
<i> But who are they?</i>

117
00:06:31,800 --> 00:06:34,467
<i>And what is it they need
from Datu Rahman?</i>

118
00:06:34,467 --> 00:06:36,433
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

119
00:06:38,700 --> 00:06:40,633
<i> Azuelo is so incompetent.</i>

120
00:06:40,800 --> 00:06:42,767
[GLOOMY MUSIC PLAYING]

121
00:06:42,867 --> 00:06:45,433
<i> Azuelo is such a joke.</i>

122
00:06:48,367 --> 00:06:51,333
<i>Someone should replace Azuelo.
My goodness.</i>

123
00:06:53,867 --> 00:06:55,800
[SLAMS TABLE]

124
00:06:59,033 --> 00:07:00,667
[LARA] You're being criticized
left and right.

125
00:07:00,667 --> 00:07:03,533
<i>The only way to solve
this case once and for all</i>

126
00:07:03,800 --> 00:07:05,533
<i>is to bring your
top agent back.</i>

127
00:07:08,567 --> 00:07:15,467
[GLOOMY MUSIC CONTINUES]

128
00:07:22,533 --> 00:07:27,333
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

129
00:07:27,667 --> 00:07:29,000
[LINE RINGING]

130
00:07:35,767 --> 00:07:36,833
Sorry.

131
00:07:43,867 --> 00:07:45,900
- [TIRES SCREECH]
- [CAR HORN HONKS]

132
00:07:45,900 --> 00:07:48,400
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

133
00:07:48,567 --> 00:07:49,567
[MAN]
Do you want to die?!

134
00:07:49,800 --> 00:07:51,267
It's my turn to go,
doofus!

135
00:07:55,033 --> 00:07:57,267
[RINGING CONTINUES]

136
00:08:02,100 --> 00:08:03,900
Make sure we get
the chance to talk

137
00:08:03,900 --> 00:08:05,600
before his cabinet meeting.

138
00:08:05,800 --> 00:08:06,867
Yes, sir.

139
00:08:17,567 --> 00:08:18,700
Right on time.

140
00:08:21,667 --> 00:08:22,867
Sharp as ever.

141
00:08:24,767 --> 00:08:25,900
Hi, Dad.

142
00:08:26,833 --> 00:08:29,767
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

143
00:08:29,767 --> 00:08:30,767
Eat.

144
00:08:35,633 --> 00:08:37,967
Senator Legazpi really
is something.

145
00:08:38,133 --> 00:08:40,433
His girlfriends get
younger and younger,

146
00:08:40,567 --> 00:08:43,900
while his hairline keeps
moving back.

147
00:08:44,567 --> 00:08:45,967
You really don't mince
your words, Dad.

148
00:08:47,067 --> 00:08:49,467
So, how are you?

149
00:08:50,233 --> 00:08:52,467
I heard the news.

150
00:08:53,167 --> 00:08:54,800
Uh, how are you holding up?

151
00:08:55,133 --> 00:08:57,900
Well, work's always
been hectic.

152
00:08:58,333 --> 00:09:01,767
Especially now we're a bit
short on manpower, but...

153
00:09:02,167 --> 00:09:03,633
I can manage.

154
00:09:04,167 --> 00:09:06,933
Tell me if Azuelo tries
to give you a hard time.

155
00:09:07,167 --> 00:09:09,067
He won't get away with it.

156
00:09:09,167 --> 00:09:10,467
No need for that, Dad.

157
00:09:10,600 --> 00:09:12,233
I'm telling you,

158
00:09:12,333 --> 00:09:14,933
he'd better not try
to mess with you.

159
00:09:15,033 --> 00:09:18,933
Or I'll remind him just how
much of a weakling he was

160
00:09:18,933 --> 00:09:20,967
during his training days.

161
00:09:21,200 --> 00:09:22,767
Come on, Dad.

162
00:09:23,700 --> 00:09:26,000
You don't have to fight
my battles for me.

163
00:09:26,100 --> 00:09:27,200
I can handle them.

164
00:09:27,200 --> 00:09:28,733
I know.

165
00:09:29,367 --> 00:09:31,967
But I just want you
to remember

166
00:09:31,967 --> 00:09:34,100
that I have your back.

167
00:09:34,900 --> 00:09:36,033
Always.

168
00:09:36,033 --> 00:09:37,100
Of course.

169
00:09:37,667 --> 00:09:39,800
You've always been there
for me, Dad.

170
00:09:39,800 --> 00:09:40,833
[MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING]

171
00:09:40,833 --> 00:09:43,033
And I will always get to call

172
00:09:43,033 --> 00:09:45,733
the great General Carillo
my dad.

173
00:09:45,733 --> 00:09:46,733
[MANUEL CHUCKLES]

174
00:09:46,733 --> 00:09:49,300
And I will always be grateful

175
00:09:49,300 --> 00:09:52,000
that you came into my life
that day.

176
00:09:52,833 --> 00:09:55,533
That I have you
for my daughter.

177
00:09:56,700 --> 00:09:58,733
I am so proud of you, dear.

178
00:09:58,733 --> 00:10:04,633
[MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]

179
00:10:04,667 --> 00:10:05,867
[JEAN] You surprised me.

180
00:10:05,867 --> 00:10:07,300
I haven't even cooked rice yet.

181
00:10:08,033 --> 00:10:09,200
It's okay.

182
00:10:09,433 --> 00:10:12,200
Here, I bought this for Erick.

183
00:10:12,533 --> 00:10:13,733
I know it's his favorite.

184
00:10:13,733 --> 00:10:16,067
Oliver used to buy one
to bring home.

185
00:10:16,367 --> 00:10:17,400
Look.

186
00:10:19,533 --> 00:10:20,833
You shouldn't have.

187
00:10:21,267 --> 00:10:22,667
I feel embarrassed.

188
00:10:23,233 --> 00:10:24,333
It's no big deal.

189
00:10:25,000 --> 00:10:26,233
I know that...

190
00:10:27,867 --> 00:10:30,067
if the situation were reversed,

191
00:10:30,233 --> 00:10:33,033
Oliver wouldn't abandon my mom.

192
00:10:33,200 --> 00:10:34,867
- [MARCUS SIGHS]
- [CLEARS THROAT]

193
00:10:34,900 --> 00:10:35,800
Uh...
[SNIFFLES]

194
00:10:35,800 --> 00:10:39,133
What's the update
on the investigation?

195
00:10:39,133 --> 00:10:42,033
Do you have any leads
as to who killed my husband?

196
00:10:43,900 --> 00:10:45,233
I'm doing my best.

197
00:10:45,233 --> 00:10:46,700
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

198
00:10:46,700 --> 00:10:48,200
I'm not going to stop.

199
00:10:51,300 --> 00:10:52,433
Me and Lara.

200
00:10:53,067 --> 00:10:54,733
Your enemy from Zamboanga,

201
00:10:54,733 --> 00:10:56,900
the person you've been after...

202
00:10:57,200 --> 00:10:59,000
Could he be the one
who killed my husband?

203
00:11:00,900 --> 00:11:02,167
I don't think so.

204
00:11:03,133 --> 00:11:04,800
I think it was another person

205
00:11:04,800 --> 00:11:07,333
or group who did this
to Oliver and the rest.

206
00:11:08,833 --> 00:11:10,100
Sorry, I'm...

207
00:11:10,633 --> 00:11:13,600
I just want to understand
everything that happened.

208
00:11:15,800 --> 00:11:18,367
He was supposed
to finally come home.

209
00:11:18,967 --> 00:11:19,867
But...

210
00:11:20,100 --> 00:11:23,067
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

211
00:11:23,500 --> 00:11:25,733
...that happened
all of a sudden.

212
00:11:28,833 --> 00:11:32,633
[JEAN CRYING]

213
00:11:35,767 --> 00:11:36,767
Sorry, sorry.

214
00:11:36,933 --> 00:11:38,133
Sorry.
[SNIFFLES]

215
00:11:38,133 --> 00:11:40,900
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

216
00:11:40,900 --> 00:11:43,200
[SOBBING]

217
00:11:46,100 --> 00:11:46,967
Oh, finally!

218
00:11:46,967 --> 00:11:50,800
I've found a tenant
for this unit.

219
00:11:50,800 --> 00:11:51,800
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

220
00:11:51,967 --> 00:11:53,567
(In Arabic) Praise be to God.

221
00:11:54,033 --> 00:11:56,267
Of course. I'm happy with it.

222
00:11:56,267 --> 00:11:57,633
The unit looks good.

223
00:11:58,700 --> 00:12:00,767
Perhaps you could
give me a tour?

224
00:12:01,200 --> 00:12:05,067
So I can get to know some
of my new neighbors.

225
00:12:05,300 --> 00:12:07,933
Sure, I'll introduce you
to them.

226
00:12:08,100 --> 00:12:10,100
Come on! Come on, hurry!
Come on!

227
00:12:13,200 --> 00:12:19,733
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

228
00:12:22,333 --> 00:12:23,367
Doc! Doc!

229
00:12:23,367 --> 00:12:25,000
Gunshot wound to the shoulder!

230
00:12:25,000 --> 00:12:26,300
Request an X-ray.

231
00:12:26,300 --> 00:12:28,333
Monitor the bleeding
and start antibiotics!

232
00:12:28,333 --> 00:12:29,300
Okay, Doc!

233
00:12:29,700 --> 00:12:34,967
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

234
00:12:36,067 --> 00:12:38,667
Radiology, request an X-ray.
Gunshot wound.

235
00:12:42,733 --> 00:12:44,000
Double IV. Fast drip.

236
00:12:44,833 --> 00:12:45,800
Request an X-ray.

237
00:12:46,067 --> 00:12:47,467
Double IV. Fast drip.

238
00:12:48,333 --> 00:12:49,467
That's a gunshot.

239
00:12:49,567 --> 00:12:51,500
Don't forget to file
a police report

240
00:12:51,500 --> 00:12:52,467
within 24 hours.

241
00:12:52,600 --> 00:12:54,800
Otherwise, you'll be charged
and lose your license.

242
00:12:54,867 --> 00:12:56,833
You don't want to waste
your medical degree.

243
00:12:57,367 --> 00:13:02,333
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

244
00:13:07,267 --> 00:13:08,367
[GROANING]

245
00:13:15,200 --> 00:13:16,933
Oh no, it broke again.

246
00:13:16,933 --> 00:13:18,333
This is beyond repair, bro.

247
00:13:18,333 --> 00:13:20,367
Next week, I'll send this to...

248
00:13:21,200 --> 00:13:22,400
What are you doing here?

249
00:13:23,867 --> 00:13:25,100
We just wanted to hang out.

250
00:13:25,400 --> 00:13:27,233
Why? Is that not allowed?

251
00:13:27,400 --> 00:13:29,167
What do you think this is?
A tourist spot?

252
00:13:29,467 --> 00:13:30,433
Go home.

253
00:13:30,900 --> 00:13:33,400
The police were looking
for this idiot here last night.

254
00:13:34,900 --> 00:13:36,367
You're probably hiding him,
aren't you?

255
00:13:36,467 --> 00:13:37,567
What?

256
00:13:38,067 --> 00:13:41,367
People like that are a plague
to society.

257
00:13:42,067 --> 00:13:43,767
They should be taught a lesson.

258
00:13:44,567 --> 00:13:46,200
- What?
- Hey!

259
00:13:46,200 --> 00:13:47,200
Easy!

260
00:13:48,567 --> 00:13:50,033
You're the real plague.

261
00:13:51,533 --> 00:13:53,233
You might want to try us.

262
00:13:53,233 --> 00:13:56,367
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

263
00:13:57,267 --> 00:14:00,900
Good thing our neighbors
are protecting us.

264
00:14:02,267 --> 00:14:03,967
Jalil is still too weak.

265
00:14:05,167 --> 00:14:08,100
He can't fight the people
hunting him yet.

266
00:14:10,333 --> 00:14:12,367
What, you wanna fight?

267
00:14:13,467 --> 00:14:14,767
Go ahead.

268
00:14:15,267 --> 00:14:16,400
Alright, leave.

269
00:14:16,600 --> 00:14:17,767
Get out.

270
00:14:17,933 --> 00:14:19,533
Go, do something useful.

271
00:14:20,433 --> 00:14:23,067
- I thought you wanted a fight?
- Don't come back, alright?

272
00:14:23,067 --> 00:14:26,900
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

273
00:14:29,200 --> 00:14:34,000
[LINE RINGING]

274
00:14:36,167 --> 00:14:37,800
[RINGING CONTINUES]

275
00:14:38,833 --> 00:14:40,467
National Law Enforcement Agency,

276
00:14:40,467 --> 00:14:41,967
<i> how may I help you?</i>

277
00:14:43,433 --> 00:14:47,833
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

278
00:14:49,300 --> 00:14:50,433
<i> Thank you.</i>

279
00:14:52,333 --> 00:14:54,000
<i> Thank you...</i>

280
00:14:54,000 --> 00:14:55,233
<i> ...so much.</i>

281
00:14:56,467 --> 00:14:57,567
<i> Hello?</i>

282
00:15:00,200 --> 00:15:01,300
<i> Hello?</i>

283
00:15:01,300 --> 00:15:04,467
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

284
00:15:15,200 --> 00:15:19,033
Sir, I've checked the bullets
you gave me.

285
00:15:19,867 --> 00:15:23,000
There are no records
in the ballistics database.

286
00:15:26,133 --> 00:15:28,700
But the striations exactly
match the bullets...

287
00:15:29,633 --> 00:15:33,300
recovered from a case
previously handled by NLEA.

288
00:15:34,900 --> 00:15:36,033
What cases?

289
00:15:37,100 --> 00:15:38,233
Human trafficking?

290
00:15:39,033 --> 00:15:40,733
<i> Based on the NLEA report,</i>

291
00:15:43,233 --> 00:15:48,500
<i>in the sea near
the Zamboanga Peninsula.</i>

292
00:15:49,533 --> 00:15:52,433
<i>That's where illegal
and smuggled firearms</i>

293
00:15:52,433 --> 00:15:54,000
<i> are being dumped.</i>

294
00:15:55,700 --> 00:15:57,467
Including drug transport cases.

295
00:15:59,100 --> 00:16:02,967
<i> Recently, our own intel has
</i>identified the exact coordinates

296
00:16:03,067 --> 00:16:05,400
<i>where contraband
is being dropped off,</i>

297
00:16:05,400 --> 00:16:07,967
<i> picked up, and hidden.</i>

298
00:16:08,700 --> 00:16:11,367
<i>Before being illegally
distributed to warlords,</i>

299
00:16:11,367 --> 00:16:13,233
<i>terrorists,
and private individuals.</i>

300
00:16:13,967 --> 00:16:18,367
So that means the people
who abducted Datu Rahman...

301
00:16:19,233 --> 00:16:21,233
are part of a larger syndicate.

302
00:16:22,300 --> 00:16:24,100
And the firearms they used

303
00:16:25,067 --> 00:16:26,933
are also part of the
smuggled weapons

304
00:16:26,933 --> 00:16:28,567
we've been tracking
for a long time.

305
00:16:28,567 --> 00:16:34,667
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

306
00:16:36,233 --> 00:16:42,367
[PHONE VIBRATING]

307
00:16:43,133 --> 00:16:44,233
Lara.

308
00:16:45,100 --> 00:16:48,567
<i>Reyes, Azuelo wants you at HQ.
Now.</i>

309
00:16:51,667 --> 00:16:58,633
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

310
00:17:06,300 --> 00:17:08,567
<i> Was my decision the right one?</i>

311
00:17:11,067 --> 00:17:13,700
<i> Did I help a good man,</i>

312
00:17:15,433 --> 00:17:17,433
<i> or a criminal?</i>

313
00:17:20,500 --> 00:17:21,633
[MAN] There he is.

314
00:17:22,333 --> 00:17:23,433
[SCOFFS]

315
00:17:24,700 --> 00:17:29,000
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

316
00:17:29,000 --> 00:17:30,433
Sir, good afternoon.

317
00:17:30,433 --> 00:17:32,500
- [AZUELO CHUCKLING]
- Good job, sir.

318
00:17:33,200 --> 00:17:34,567
There he is, sir.

319
00:17:35,633 --> 00:17:41,133
- [APPLAUSE]
- [CHEERING]

320
00:17:41,133 --> 00:17:48,133
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

321
00:17:50,800 --> 00:17:52,267
Sir, what's the meaning of this?

322
00:17:52,500 --> 00:17:54,600
Welcome back, Agent Reyes.

323
00:17:55,867 --> 00:17:58,733
Lara told me you were
the one who led us

324
00:17:58,733 --> 00:18:00,800
to Datu Rahman's hideout.

325
00:18:01,200 --> 00:18:02,467
Because of that,

326
00:18:02,467 --> 00:18:04,700
I'd like to personally
congratulate you.

327
00:18:06,833 --> 00:18:08,700
Your suspension has been lifted.

328
00:18:09,700 --> 00:18:11,933
You may now report for work.

329
00:18:12,633 --> 00:18:18,800
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

330
00:18:18,800 --> 00:18:20,133
Thank you, sir.

331
00:18:21,400 --> 00:18:25,700
Your first mission
is to find and arrest

332
00:18:25,933 --> 00:18:27,800
Datu Rahman's accomplice.

333
00:18:28,233 --> 00:18:32,700
Because that's how
we'll catch him.

334
00:18:35,833 --> 00:18:37,700
Don't fail me, Agent Reyes.

335
00:18:38,367 --> 00:18:39,567
Yes, sir.

336
00:18:41,200 --> 00:18:48,133
[APPLAUDING, CHEERING]

337
00:18:56,433 --> 00:18:58,433
Come here.

338
00:18:59,300 --> 00:19:00,533
This is...

339
00:19:00,700 --> 00:19:03,867
my favorite halal food place.

340
00:19:04,067 --> 00:19:05,733
The owner's name is Ibrahim.

341
00:19:05,733 --> 00:19:08,367
The food there is very good.

342
00:19:09,300 --> 00:19:11,433
- Assalaamu alikum.
- Salam.

343
00:19:11,567 --> 00:19:13,767
The food looks really good.

344
00:19:14,933 --> 00:19:19,533
Sure, I'll stop by when
I'm too lazy to cook.

345
00:19:19,533 --> 00:19:20,900
That's great.

346
00:19:21,133 --> 00:19:23,233
That's right.
Okay, we'll go now.

347
00:19:23,233 --> 00:19:25,300
Come on, let's go here next.

348
00:19:25,300 --> 00:19:27,800
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

349
00:19:27,800 --> 00:19:29,567
Oh, here.

350
00:19:30,133 --> 00:19:32,267
This is Ida's house.

351
00:19:33,267 --> 00:19:34,200
Ida!

352
00:19:34,300 --> 00:19:35,667
Ida! Oh, gosh!

353
00:19:35,667 --> 00:19:37,100
This is my new tenant.

354
00:19:37,300 --> 00:19:39,833
- He'll be our new neighbor.
- [IDA LAUGHS]

355
00:19:39,833 --> 00:19:41,867
Hello, hello, how are you?

356
00:19:42,067 --> 00:19:44,300
Welcome to our area.

357
00:19:44,833 --> 00:19:46,200
Thank you.

358
00:19:47,733 --> 00:19:49,767
- Your place looks beautiful.
- [LAUGHTER]

359
00:19:50,433 --> 00:19:51,800
Can I take a look?

360
00:19:51,800 --> 00:19:53,267
- [IDA] Oh, yes! Alright!
- Let's go inside.

361
00:19:53,267 --> 00:19:54,667
Sure, come inside.

362
00:19:54,667 --> 00:19:55,900
You go first!
This is your house.

363
00:19:55,900 --> 00:19:57,733
- Oh, yeah!
- [LAUGHTER]

364
00:19:57,733 --> 00:20:00,933
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

365
00:20:00,933 --> 00:20:03,133
[GUN COCKS]

366
00:20:08,300 --> 00:20:09,767
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

367
00:20:18,800 --> 00:20:20,400
You should buy me coffee.

368
00:20:21,000 --> 00:20:22,800
- Looks like you missed me.
- [SCOFFS]

369
00:20:23,000 --> 00:20:24,833
You hate staying away
from me, don't you?

370
00:20:25,100 --> 00:20:26,767
You look like you
might thank me.

371
00:20:26,867 --> 00:20:28,267
That's fine too.

372
00:20:28,833 --> 00:20:29,900
Lara.

373
00:20:31,600 --> 00:20:32,733
Thank you.

374
00:20:34,167 --> 00:20:37,333
This mission is becoming
too personal to you, so...

375
00:20:37,633 --> 00:20:40,367
I'm sorry, but I'm going
to keep an eye on you.

376
00:20:40,867 --> 00:20:42,800
I have to keep you
on a short leash.

377
00:20:43,967 --> 00:20:46,800
Unfortunately, I have to keep
an eye on your every move.

378
00:20:47,500 --> 00:20:48,700
Understood?

379
00:20:50,300 --> 00:20:51,467
Yes, ma'am.

380
00:20:52,833 --> 00:20:54,233
Good to have you back.

381
00:20:54,233 --> 00:21:01,267
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

382
00:21:05,533 --> 00:21:07,267
[FELIX] Thank you. Salam.

383
00:21:07,667 --> 00:21:09,333
Let's go here. Here!

384
00:21:09,367 --> 00:21:10,833
Hurry up. [CHUCKLES]

385
00:21:12,600 --> 00:21:13,967
Come here.

386
00:21:14,667 --> 00:21:16,000
Do you see that?

387
00:21:17,367 --> 00:21:19,033
Omar lives there.

388
00:21:19,033 --> 00:21:21,300
He's in charge
of our community.

389
00:21:22,433 --> 00:21:24,233
- Ah, really?
- [ZUBINA CHUCKLES]

390
00:21:24,233 --> 00:21:27,200
I think it would be great
if I met Omar.

391
00:21:27,700 --> 00:21:29,400
That's a great idea.

392
00:21:29,400 --> 00:21:30,900
Come on. Hurry up. [CHUCKLES]

393
00:21:30,900 --> 00:21:37,867
[UNEASY MUSIC PLAYING]

394
00:21:40,433 --> 00:21:42,500
- C'mon, hurry up!
- Okay.

395
00:21:42,533 --> 00:21:44,033
- Hurry up!
- [RASHID] Look at that!

396
00:21:44,033 --> 00:21:46,633
[MALIK] I told you!
I have two years to pay it off.

397
00:21:46,633 --> 00:21:48,467
Rashid! Malik! What is that?

398
00:21:48,467 --> 00:21:49,900
[MALIK] I'm showing off
my motorcycle.

399
00:21:49,900 --> 00:21:52,033
- C'mon, come here.
- It needs to be repaired.

400
00:21:52,033 --> 00:21:54,300
I wonder where Omar is.

401
00:21:54,300 --> 00:21:55,900
- [SCREAMS]
- Hey!

402
00:21:57,900 --> 00:21:59,200
What happened?

403
00:21:59,567 --> 00:22:00,400
Oh gosh!

404
00:22:00,933 --> 00:22:01,933
Wait...

405
00:22:02,567 --> 00:22:03,600
I know you.

406
00:22:03,800 --> 00:22:05,033
You're the police!

407
00:22:05,367 --> 00:22:07,367
[SCREAMING]

408
00:22:07,367 --> 00:22:09,333
- Oh gosh!
- Don't come near!

409
00:22:09,800 --> 00:22:11,067
Don't come near!

410
00:22:11,467 --> 00:22:13,300
[FELIX] Go ahead! Try me!

411
00:22:13,300 --> 00:22:15,267
Will you come near me?
Go ahead!

412
00:22:15,600 --> 00:22:16,967
A lot of people will die.

413
00:22:16,967 --> 00:22:20,200
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

414
00:22:20,400 --> 00:22:21,433
[FELIX] Go ahead.

415
00:22:22,300 --> 00:22:23,567
Huh?

416
00:22:24,467 --> 00:22:26,433
Go ahead! Come close!

417
00:22:26,567 --> 00:22:33,433
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

418
00:22:47,600 --> 00:22:50,433
<i>Here are the candidates for
the new task force alpha.</i>

419
00:22:50,467 --> 00:22:51,833
<i> You need to choose four.</i>

420
00:22:51,833 --> 00:22:53,533
<i> I will choose my own team.</i>

421
00:22:53,533 --> 00:22:56,600
<i>I need people I can trust.
You know that!</i>

422
00:22:56,800 --> 00:23:00,467
If something happens to <i> all of
</i> you, I won't forgive myself.

423
00:23:00,467 --> 00:23:02,100
<i>- Jamilah!
- You still have an injury!</i>

424
00:23:02,100 --> 00:23:04,400
<i>People are already
looking for you.</i>

425
00:23:04,633 --> 00:23:06,633
<i>My conscience
can't handle it.</i>

426
00:23:08,367 --> 00:23:10,133
<i>- What do you know?
- He said he saw a van</i>

427
00:23:10,133 --> 00:23:12,133
<i>that came out of
the Greenmile Warehouse.</i>

428
00:23:12,133 --> 00:23:13,333
<i>This was the only picture
he took.</i>

429
00:23:13,533 --> 00:23:15,933
<i>The plate number starts
with N, then 475.</i>

430
00:23:16,133 --> 00:23:19,467
<i> My car got stolen 3 days ago.</i>

431
00:23:19,467 --> 00:23:22,333
<i>Do your cars have
a GPS tracking device, sir?</i>

432
00:23:22,367 --> 00:23:23,033
<i> Yes, they do.</i>

433
00:23:24,133 --> 00:23:25,133
<i> I'm also tracking Datu Rahman.</i>

434
00:23:25,400 --> 00:23:28,867
<i>I need to find him to prove
that I didn't let him escape.</i>

435
00:23:30,000 --> 00:23:32,433
<i> She's our new nurse.</i>

436
00:23:33,667 --> 00:23:35,100
<i> Nice meeting you, Ma'am.</i>

437
00:23:35,367 --> 00:23:36,967
<i> My name is Jamilah.</i>

438
00:23:37,133 --> 00:23:38,633
<i>But we still shouldn't
be complacent.</i>

439
00:23:38,633 --> 00:23:40,067
<i>We don't know what
they're capable of doing</i>

440
00:23:40,067 --> 00:23:41,667
<i> to hide Datu Rahman.</i>

441
00:23:41,867 --> 00:23:42,833
<i> Lara?</i>

442
00:23:43,667 --> 00:23:44,700
<i> Where are you?</i>

443
00:23:45,133 --> 00:23:46,800
<i> I'm at the Zylverix Building.</i>

444
00:23:47,000 --> 00:23:48,933
<i>I've already found where
they took Datu Rahman.</i>

445
00:23:49,133 --> 00:23:51,700
<i>Didn't I tell you to update me
on your every move?!</i>

446
00:23:53,200 --> 00:23:54,800
<i> I will find out the truth.</i>

447
00:23:55,000 --> 00:23:57,067
<i> You're going to pay
for what you did to my father</i>

448
00:23:57,267 --> 00:23:59,033
<i> and to our whole village!</i>
